AGAIN, I will restate...<br>
if its an abuse of the system, as you stated above...as *I* stated in my own post using almost the same exact words (except I used '5' and you used '7'), if it is an abuse of the system, that is one issue and if someone is getting 7 (or 5 or 2) rotations on something where they would have one, I am completely with you !  That would be an abuse of the system.<br>
<br>
The part that 'doesn't make sense' as you put it is that some people want to tie up moral conceptions of 'pride', 'earning' and moral rewards into the picture.  That's all I am arguing against.  Oh, it's a great debating tactic.  I mean its the way they tack riders on to bills in our own government, adding a side item that is more likely to be opposed to the issue that is a sure bet.<br>
<br>
However, if the RTA is not about determining what guilds should get what rewards, based on a groups view of what has been earned, then neither should the argument be.<br>
