That means there are players who play to see the end content. Some may not have the time needed to be hardcore enough to get into a capable guild but are still fine players and want to see end content. With restrictions like these your basically saying &quot;Sorry, if you can't kill the mob with your own guild then you will not be able to kill it and enter our zone&quot; and that could be enough reason to quit. I for one would quit eq if my progress was limited. What's the point of a progression based game with no progression opportunities? None.<br>
<br>
Karadin Said:<br>
&quot;That’s just it, it’s not two issues, it’s one issue, that certain guilds are looking to manipulate the spirit of the rotations through a technical loophole that these mobs aren’t actually on rotation, but under past historic precedent, would be.&quot; <br>
