<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.drow.org" target="top">Blood of the Spider</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mianiel>Mianiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/25/03 7:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=137>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Those that are arguing that teaming to beat POP bosses doesn't get that team loot are missing the point.  The &quot;loot&quot; is advancing to higher planes with better xp (in most cases though some zones are really raid only), and much better loot.  The loot that is dropped on practically any mob in the game isn't worth that.  Say you have 72 people from 3 guilds at a raid and you split the real drops 3 ways that means 1 person will be getting a drop per guild.  But you don't split that higher zone access that way (which in turn allows ALL of those 72 better xp and loot).  Arguing this otherwise is untrue.<br>
<br>
Soe did this on purpose, POP is a linear (mostly) design that has bottlenecks.  Once your guild (or alliance) passes this bottleneck then you are rewarded with better XP and better loot.  Teaming up on a POP bottleneck gives the people on the raid FAR FAR more reward than teaming on any Mob, rotation or otherwise.  If you are going to team up and split the negligible real loots from these fights and then resplit into separate entities on rotation mobs and in the higher planes you now have access to, that is getting around the split of the system that has been established on the Rathe and has made this server one of the best in the game.<br>
<br>
Anyway, with the flagging changes we have seen, alliances will be much tougher.  Either you will have to have 72 or less, or risk MAJOR fights on who is flagged or who isn't.<br>
<br>
